The paper discusses adversarial attacks on deep learning models, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a novel method for optimizing adversarial attacks using genetic algorithms. The second likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the vulnerability of deep learning models to adversarial attacks and proposes a defense mechanism. The third likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as adversarial attacks are often used to evaluate the robustness of image classification models. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms to optimize adversarial attacks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper proposes a method for optimizing adversarial attacks using genetic algorithms, which is a type of evolutionary algorithm.
